    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p> <p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the <strong>coconut cream</strong> from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop it roughly, then dissolve\u00a0in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>broccoli</strong>\u00a0into quarters, lengthways</p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p> <p>Add the <strong>broccoli quarters</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on both sides or until golden brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>browned broccoli</strong> quarters to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 8 min or until the broccoli is tender\u00a0\u2013 this is your<strong> charred broccoli</strong></p> <p>Reserve the pan</p> <p>Whilst the broccoli is cooking, pat the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper </strong>and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until they're browned and cooked through</p> <p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked steaks</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and set aside to rest for 2 min</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steaks are cooking, add the <strong>coconut stock</strong>,\u00a0<strong>peanut butte</strong>r,\u00a0<strong>soy sauce</strong> and the<strong> chilli jam</strong> to a pot over a medium heat and whisk until smooth</p> <p>Cook for 3-4 min or until thickened, stirring more or less continuously, then remove the pot from the heat \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>peanut sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested</strong>\u00a0<strong>pork </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-peanut-sauce-and-charred-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced pork </strong>on top of\u00a0the <strong>cooked</strong>\u00a0<strong>rice</strong>\u00a0with the\u00a0<strong>charred broccoli</strong> to the side</p> <p>Drizzle the <strong>peanut sauce</strong> all over</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
